From: tonytranrp <100391458+tonytranrp@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sun, 14 Jun 2026 22:26:07 -1000
Subject: [PATCH] clang-mg: add compact bail-condition coverage tests

Granular -fdump-record-layouts tests asserting that compact leaves a record in SOURCE order when it must bail: bit-fields, polymorphic (vptr), base class, and anonymous struct member (IndirectFieldDecl). Each struct is shaped so source order differs from the reordered order, making the assertion meaningful. No compiler change.


diff --git a/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-bail-anonymous-member.cpp b/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-bail-anonymous-member.cpp
new file mode 100644
index 000000000..e16635d12
--- /dev/null
+++ b/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-bail-anonymous-member.cpp
@@ -0,0 +1,18 @@
+// A `compact` struct with an anonymous struct member (which projects
+// IndirectFieldDecls) is left in SOURCE order -- reorder bails to avoid moving
+// fields out from under the projection. If it had sorted by alignment, the
+// `char` fields would move to the tail; here `small` must stay first.
+//
+// RUN: %clang_cc1 -std=c++20 -fcxxmg -fsyntax-only -fdump-record-layouts %s | FileCheck %s
+
+compact struct S {
+  char small;
+  struct { int x; double y; };
+  char tail;
+};
+S s; // force layout computation
+
+// `small` (first source field) must precede `tail` (last source field); both
+// names are unique to the outer record's dump. Source order is preserved.
+// CHECK: char small
+// CHECK: char tail
diff --git a/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-bail-base-class.cpp b/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-bail-base-class.cpp
new file mode 100644
index 000000000..e1a40d75c
--- /dev/null
+++ b/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-bail-base-class.cpp
@@ -0,0 +1,19 @@
+// A `compact` struct with a base class is left in SOURCE order -- reorder bails
+// because base subobjects must lay out first and mixing them with field
+// reordering is unsafe. If it had sorted by alignment, `big` would precede
+// `small`.
+//
+// RUN: %clang_cc1 -std=c++20 -fcxxmg -fsyntax-only -fdump-record-layouts %s | FileCheck %s
+
+struct Base { int x; };
+
+compact struct S : Base {
+  char small;
+  double big;
+};
+S s; // force layout computation
+
+// CHECK: struct S
+// CHECK: struct Base (base)
+// CHECK: char small
+// CHECK-NEXT: double big
diff --git a/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-bail-bitfield.cpp b/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-bail-bitfield.cpp
new file mode 100644
index 000000000..88a720099
--- /dev/null
+++ b/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-bail-bitfield.cpp
@@ -0,0 +1,17 @@
+// A `compact` struct containing a bit-field is left in SOURCE order -- reorder
+// bails on bit-fields (their packing is order-sensitive). If it had sorted by
+// descending alignment, `big` (double) would move ahead of `small` (char).
+//
+// RUN: %clang_cc1 -std=c++20 -fcxxmg -fsyntax-only -fdump-record-layouts %s | FileCheck %s
+
+compact struct S {
+  char small;
+  int flags : 4;
+  double big;
+};
+S s; // force layout computation
+
+// CHECK: struct S
+// CHECK-NEXT: char small
+// CHECK-NEXT: int flags
+// CHECK-NEXT: double big
diff --git a/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-bail-polymorphic.cpp b/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-bail-polymorphic.cpp
new file mode 100644
index 000000000..094648b33
--- /dev/null
+++ b/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-bail-polymorphic.cpp
@@ -0,0 +1,17 @@
+// A polymorphic `compact` struct (has a virtual function, hence a vptr) is left
+// in SOURCE order -- reorder bails so the vptr and subobject layout are not
+// disturbed. If it had sorted by alignment, `big` would precede `small`.
+//
+// RUN: %clang_cc1 -std=c++20 -fcxxmg -fsyntax-only -fdump-record-layouts %s | FileCheck %s
+
+compact struct S {
+  char small;
+  double big;
+  virtual void f();
+};
+S s; // force layout computation
+
+// CHECK: struct S
+// CHECK-NEXT: (S vftable pointer)
+// CHECK-NEXT: char small
+// CHECK-NEXT: double big
-- 
